From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] soc: qcom: eud: aurora: don't abort enable_eud() on secure-EUD failure

On a production Pixel Watch 2 the TrustZone monitor rejects the
secure-EUD enable (qcom_scm_io_writel -> rc:-22). enable_eud() then
returns early, before its final extcon_set_state_sync(EXTCON_USB,
true), leaving EUD's extcon stuck "disconnected". dwc3-msm is wired to
the EUD extcon (its google,extcon-usb-shim phandle has no driver, see
dwc3-msm-force-peripheral.patch), so it never sees a USB attach and no
UDC is created -> USB/adb dead.

The secure step only gates EUD's own debug endpoint, which is unusable
on production anyway. Log the failure but continue so the EXTCON_USB
attach event is still asserted -- that is all dwc3-msm needs.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora bring-up]
Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/soc/qcom/eud.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/qcom/eud.c
@@ -180,11 +180,19 @@
 	if (priv->secure_eud_en && !check_eud_mode_mgr2(priv)) {
 		ret = qcom_scm_io_writel(priv->eud_mode_mgr2_phys_base +
 				   EUD_REG_EUD_EN2, EUD_ENABLE_CMD);
-		if (ret) {
+		if (ret)
+			/*
+			 * aurora: on production the TZ monitor rejects the
+			 * secure-EUD enable (rc:-22). That only gates EUD's
+			 * own debug endpoint, which is unusable here anyway.
+			 * Do NOT return: fall through so the EXTCON_USB=true
+			 * below is still asserted -- that extcon event is the
+			 * only thing dwc3-msm needs to bring the USB gadget
+			 * (adb) up on this watch.
+			 */
 			dev_err(&pdev->dev,
-			"qcom_scm_io_writel failed with rc:%d\n", ret);
-			return;
-		}
+			"qcom_scm_io_writel failed rc:%d (non-fatal; EUD extcon still drives USB attach)\n",
+			ret);
 	}
 
 	/* Ensure Register Writes Complete */
